{"sessionId":"097a63cf-f510-4110-b827-ef9740062d44","timestamp":1773607435150,"cwd":"/home/runner/work/linkshortener/linkshortener","toolName":"bash","toolArgs":"{\"command\": \"cat /tmp/copilot-tool-output-1773607429784-4fscms.txt | head -500\", \"description\": \"Read exploration output part 1\"}","toolResult":{"resultType":"success","textResultForLlm":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## **COMPREHENSIVE REPOSITORY EXPLORATION REPORT**\n\n---\n\n## **1. REPOSITORY STRUCTURE OVERVIEW**\n\n### **Root Layout**\n```\nlinkshortener/\n├── backend/              # Go backend (Gin + Huma framework)\n├── frontend/             # Vue 3 + TypeScript frontend\n├── openapi/              # OpenAPI spec (auto-generated)\n├── ai-instructions/      # Agent guidelines (7 files)\n├── sql/                  # Database migrations (PostgreSQL)\n├── commands/             # CLI utilities\n├── docker-compose.yaml   # Local development setup\n└── Makefile              # Build commands\n```\n\n---\n\n## **2. FRONTEND ARCHITECTURE**\n\n### **2.1 Directory Structure**\n\n**`/frontend/src/views/`** (4 files)\n- **DashboardView.vue** - Main authenticated dashboard page with URL management\n- **HomeView.vue** - Simple public landing page\n- **AuthCallbackView.vue** - OAuth callback handler\n- **AuthCallbackView.spec.ts** - Tests\n\n**`/frontend/src/components/`**\n- **`ui/`** - shadcn/vue components (6 installed):\n  - `badge/` - Status badges (Active/Expired)\n  - `button/` - Action buttons\n  - `dialog/` - Modal dialogs (Create Link dialog)\n  - `input/` - Form inputs\n  - `table/` - Data table display\n  - `tooltip/` - Hover tooltips\n\n**`/frontend/src/stores/`** (Pinia)\n- **urls.ts** - URL management state (create, list, fetch)\n- **auth.ts** - Authentication state (login, logout, JWT)\n- **theme.ts** - Theme state\n\n**`/frontend/src/lib/`**\n- **`api/`** - OpenAPI-generated client (auto-generated from backend spec)\n  - `services/DefaultService.ts` - API methods for all endpoints\n  - `models/` - TypeScript types for requests/responses\n  - `core/` - HTTP client infrastructure\n- **config.ts** - App configuration\n- **utils.ts** - Helper functions\n\n### **2.2 Dashboard Page (DashboardView.vue)**\n\n**Key Features:**\n- List shortened URLs in table (desktop) or card layout (mobile)\n- Create new link dialog with:\n  - Long URL (required)\n  - Optional shortcode (exactly 6 chars)\n  - Optional expiry date\n- Pagination (page + page_size)\n- Status badges (Active/Expired)\n- Responsive design (mobile-first)\n\n**State Management:**\n```typescript\n// urls.ts store\ninterface UrlsState {\n  items: UrlItem[]           // URL list\n  total: number              // Total count for pagination\n  page: number               // Current page\n  pageSize: number           // Items per page\n  loading: boolean           // List loading state\n  error: string | null       // List error message\n  creating: boolean          // Create in progress\n  createError: string | null // Create error message\n}\n\n// Key actions:\nfetchUrls(page?, pageSize?)  // GET /user/urls\ncreateUrl(params)            // POST /user/urls\n```\n\n**API Calls Flow:**\n1. Frontend calls `DefaultService.listUserUrls()` \n2. Service makes HTTP GET to `/user/urls?page=X&page_size=Y`\n3. Backend returns `ListUrlsResponseBody` with items array\n4. Store updates `items`, `total`, `page`, `pageSize`\n\n### **2.3 shadcn/vue Components Used**\n\n**Strict Rules (from frontend-components.md):**\n- Only shadcn/vue components allowed (no custom UI components unless explicitly requested)\n- No component modifications allowed (use as-is)\n- Compose components directly in views (no wrapper components)\n- All UI styling via Tailwind CSS utility classes only\n\n**Current Components:**\n- `Button` - Primary/outline/ghost variants\n- `Input` - Text and datetime-local inputs\n- `Dialog` - Modal with DialogContent, DialogHeader, DialogTitle, DialogDescription, DialogFooter\n- `Table` - TableHeader, TableHead, TableBody, TableRow, TableCell, TableEmpty\n- `Badge` - Status display (variant=\"destructive\", variant=\"secondary\")\n- Icons from `lucide-vue-next` (ChevronDown, ChevronUp)\n\n---\n\n## **3. BACKEND ARCHITECTURE**\n\n### **3.1 Backend Directory Structure**\n\n**`/backend/web/`** - HTTP layer (Huma framework)\n- **routes/**\n  - `urls.go` - URL management endpoints (2 registered)\n  - `auth.go` - OAuth and auth endpoints\n  - `middleware.go` - JWT validation middleware\n  - `errors.go` - Error mapping function\n- **viewmodels/**\n  - `url.go` - Request/response DTOs\n- **mappers/**\n  - `url.go` - ViewModel ↔ business model conversion\n\n**`/backend/business-logic/`** - Business logic layer\n- **handlers/**\n  - `url_handler.go` - URL management business logic\n  - `auth_handler.go` - Auth business logic\n- **interfaces/**\n  - `url_repository.go` - Repository contract\n  - `shortcode_generator.go` - Generator interface\n  - `user_repository.go` - User data contract\n- **models/**\n  - `url.go` - `ShortenedUrl` struct (no ORM tags, pure Go)\n  - `auth.go`, `user.go`, `user_provider.go`\n- **Validators & Generators**\n  - `url_validator.go` - Long URL validation (length, scheme, SSRF checks)\n  - `shortcode.go` - Base62 generator + custom shortcode validation\n\n**`/backend/infrastructure/pg/`** - Database layer\n- **models/**\n  - `shortened_url.go` - Bun ORM model (with tags)\n  - `user.go`, `user_provider.go`, `url_click.go`\n- **repositories/**\n  - `url_repository.go` - SQL implementation\n  - `user_repository.go`\n- **migrations/**\n  - `001_initial_schema.go` - Schema setup\n- **mappings/**\n  - `shortened_url.go` - DB model ↔ business model conversion\n- **seed/** - Dev-mode sample data\n\n### **3.2 Currently Implemented Endpoints**\n\n| Method | Path | OperationID | Summary | Auth |\n|--------|------|-------------|---------|------|\n| **GET** | `/user/urls` | list-user-urls | List user's shortened URLs | ✓ JWT |\n| **POST** | `/user/urls` | create-shortened-url | Create new shortened URL | ✓ JWT |\n| **POST** | `/auth/register` | register-user | Complete new-user registration | ✗ Public |\n| **POST** | `/auth/logout` | logout | Blacklist JWT and log out | ✓ JWT |\n\n**Missing (No Delete/Edit):**\n- ❌ `DELETE /user/urls/{id}` - Delete URL\n- ❌ `PATCH /user/urls/{id}` - Edit URL (long_url, shortcode, expires_at)\n- ❌ `GET /user/urls/{id}` - Get single URL details\n\n### **3.3 Create URL Flow (Existing Implementation)**\n\n**Frontend:**\n```typescript\n// DashboardView.vue\nasync function submitCreate() {\n  const result = await urlsStore.createUrl({\n    longUrl: longUrl.value,\n    shortcode: shortcodeField.value.trim() || undefined,\n    expiresAt: expiresAt.value ? new Date(expiresAt.value).toISOString() : undefined,\n  })\n  if (result !== null) {\n    dialogOpen.value = false\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**API Client:**\n```typescript\n// DefaultService.ts (auto-generated)\npublic static createUrl({\n  requestBody,\n}: {\n  requestBody?: CreateUrlRequestBody,\n}): CancelablePromise<CreateUrlResponseBody | ErrorModel> {\n  return __request(OpenAPI, {\n    method: 'POST',\n    url: '/user/urls',\n    body: requestBody,\n    mediaType: 'application/json',\n  });\n}\n```\n\n**Backend Route Handler:**\n```go\n// routes/urls.go\nhuma.Register(api, huma.Operation{\n  OperationID:   \"create-shortened-url\",\n  Method:        http.MethodPost,\n  Path:          \"/user/urls\",\n  DefaultStatus: http.StatusCreated,\n}, func(ctx context.Context, input *viewmodels.CreateUrlInput) (*viewmodels.CreateUrlResponse, error) {\n  claims := GetJWTClaimsFromContext(ctx)\n  created, err := h.CreateUrl(ctx, claims.UserID, input.Body.LongUrl, input.Body.Shortcode, input.Body.ExpiresAt)\n  if err != nil {\n    return nil, MapError(err)\n  }\n  baseUrl := os.Getenv(\"APP_BASE_URL\")\n  return &viewmodels.CreateUrlResponse{\n    Body: webmappers.CreateUrlToResponse(created, baseUrl),\n  }, nil\n})\n```\n\n**Business Logic Handler:**\n```go\n// handlers/url_handler.go\nfunc (h *UrlHandler) CreateUrl(ctx context.Context, userID int64, longUrl string, \n  customShortcode *string, expiresAt *time.Time) (*bizmodels.ShortenedUrl, error) {\n  \n  // Validate long URL\n  if err := businesslogic.ValidateLongUrl(longUrl, h.maxUrlLen); err != nil {\n    return nil, err\n  }\n  \n  // If custom shortcode provided, validate it\n  if customShortcode != nil {\n    if err := businesslogic.ValidateCustomShortcode(*customShortcode, ...); err != nil {\n      return nil, err\n    }\n    // Create with custom shortcode\n  } else {\n    // Generate and retry on collision\n    for attempt := 0; attempt < h.maxShortcodeRetries; attempt++ {\n      sc, _ := h.generator.GenerateShortcode()\n      created, err := h.urls.Create(ctx, record)\n      if err == nil {\n        return created, nil\n      }\n      if !errors.Is(err, businesslogic.ErrConflict) {\n        return nil, err\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Database Repository:**\n```go\n// infrastructure/pg/repositories/url_repository.go\nfunc (r *UrlRepository) Create(ctx context.Context, url *bizmodels.ShortenedUrl) (*bizmodels.ShortenedUrl, error) {\n  dbModel := mappings.ToDbModel(url)\n  if err := r.db.NewInsert().Model(dbModel).Scan(ctx); err != nil {\n    // Check if UNIQUE constraint violation (shortcode collision) → return ErrConflict\n    return nil, err\n  }\n  return mappings.ToBusinessModel(dbModel), nil\n}\n```\n\n### **3.4 Delete URL Flow (NOT YET IMPLEMENTED)**\n\n**What needs to be added:**\n\n**Frontend:** Button in URL row → confirmation dialog → API call\n**API:** `DELETE /user/urls/{id}`\n**Backend Handler:** Check ownership → delete from DB\n**Database:** Delete by ID\n\n### **3.5 Edit URL Flow (NOT YET IMPLEMENTED)**\n\n**What needs to be added:**\n\n**Frontend:** Edit button → modal form → API call\n**API:** `PATCH /user/urls/{id}` with request body\n**Backend Handler:** Validate new values → check ownership → update DB\n**Database:** Update fields by ID\n\n### **3.6 Data Models**\n\n**Business Logic Model:**\n```go\n// business-logic/models/url.go\ntype ShortenedUrl struct {\n  ID        int64\n  UserID    int64\n  Shortcode string\n  LongUrl   string\n  ExpiresAt *time.Time\n  CreatedAt time.Time\n  UpdatedAt time.Time\n}\n```\n\n**Viewmodel (Request):**\n```go\n// web/viewmodels/url.go\ntype CreateUrlRequestBody struct {\n  LongUrl   string     `json:\"long_url\" required:\"true\"`\n  Shortcode *string    `json:\"shortcode,omitempty\"` // 6 chars optional\n  ExpiresAt *time.Time `json:\"expires_at,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Viewmodel (Response):**\n```go\ntype CreateUrlResponseBody struct {\n  ID        int64      `json:\"id\"`\n  Shortcode string     `json:\"shortcode\"`\n  LongUrl   string     `json:\"long_url\"`\n  ShortUrl  string     `json:\"short_url\"` // baseUrl + \"/r/\" + shortcode\n  ExpiresAt *time.Time `json:\"expires_at,omitempty\"`\n  CreatedAt time.Time  `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n```\n\n**TypeScript Types (generated):**\n```typescript\n// frontend/src/lib/api/models/UrlItem.ts\nexport type UrlItem = {\n  created_at: string;\n  expires_at?: string;\n  id: number;\n  long_url: string;\n  shortcode: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n};\n```\n\n### **3.7 Error Handling**\n\n**Business Logic Sentinel Errors:**\n```go\nvar (\n  ErrNotFound    = errors.New(\"not found\")     // → 404\n  ErrConflict    = errors.New(\"conflict\")      // → 409 (shortcode already used)\n  ErrValidation  = errors.New(\"validation error\") // → 400\n  ErrExpired     = errors.New(\"expired\")       // → 410\n  ErrUnauthorized = errors.New(\"unauthorized\")  // → 403\n)\n```\n\n**Error Mapping (in routes/errors.go):**\n```go\nfunc MapError(err error) error {\n  switch {\n  case errors.Is(err, businesslogic.ErrNotFound):\n    return huma.Error404NotFound(\"resource not found\")\n  case errors.Is(err, businesslogic.ErrConflict):\n    return huma.Error409Conflict(\"resource already exists\")\n  case errors.Is(err, businesslogic.ErrValidation):\n    return huma.Error400BadRequest(err.Error())\n  case errors.Is(err, businesslogic.ErrExpired):\n    return huma.Error410Gone(\"resource has expired\")\n  default:\n    return huma.Error500InternalServerError(\"internal server error\")\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### **3.8 Validation Rules**\n\n**Long URL Validation (url_validator.go):**\n- Must be ≤ 2048 characters\n- Must parse as valid URL\n- Scheme must be http or https\n- Host must not be localhost or loopback (127.0.0.1, ::1)\n- Host must not resolve to private IP (10.x, 172.16–31.x, 192.168.x) → SSRF prevention\n\n**Custom Shortcode Validation (shortcode.go):**\n- Must be 6 characters (configurable min/max)\n- Only alphanumeric + hyphens allowed\n- Must not match reserved words: auth, login, logout, admin, user, api, docs, static, public, assets, css, js, img, health, status, ping, robots\n\n**Auto-Generated Shortcode:**\n- Base62 encoding (0-9A-Za-z) exactly 6 characters\n- Collision retry up to MAX_SHORTCODE_RETRIES (default: configurable)\n\n---\n\n## **4. AI INSTRUCTION FILES**\n\n### **4.1 frontend-components.md**\n**Key Rules:**\n- **Only shadcn/vue** is permitted for UI components\n- Never create custom components without explicit user approval\n- Compose primitives directly in views (no wrapper components)\n- All styling via Tailwind CSS utility classes only\n- `<script setup lang=\"ts\">` mandatory (Composition API)\n- shadcn/vue components in `src/components/` are excluded from test coverage (used as-is)\n\n### **4.2 frontend-ui-ux.md**\n**Key Rules:**\n- Consistency: same colors, fonts, spacing across app\n- Accessibility: semantic HTML, keyboard navigation, WCAG 2.1 AA contrast\n- Responsive: mobile-first, 44×44px touch targets\n- Navigation: shallow (max 2 interactions to reach any function)\n- Feedback: loading states, error messages, success confirmations\n- Visual hierarchy: whitespace, typography levels, single primary CTA per section\n\n### **4.3 backend-business.md**\n**Key Rules:**\n- **Pure Go business logic** in `business-logic/handlers/`\n- Models are plain structs (no ORM tags)\n- Interfaces in `business-logic/interfaces/`\n- Handlers use **constructor injection** of dependencies\n- Return **sentinel errors** (ErrNotFound, ErrValidation, etc.)\n- Validation: URL format, shortcode rules, SSRF checks, expiration\n- All handlers + interfaces must have **95% code coverage**\n\n### **4.4 backend-web.md**\n**Key Rules:**\n- **Zero business logic** in web layer\n- Route handlers follow: map request → call handler → map response\n- Viewmodels with `json` and `validate` tags only\n- Mappers for all viewmodel ↔ business model conversions\n- Huma registration with OperationID, Method, Path, Summary\n- Error mapping: business errors → HTTP responses\n- Pagination: `page` and `page_size` query params\n\n### **4.5 backend-dblayer.md**\n**Key Rules:**\n- **PostgreSQL + Bun ORM** (uptrace/bun)\n- DB models with `bun` tags in `infrastructure/pg/models/`\n- Repository interfaces in `business-logic/interfaces/`\n- Repository implementations in `infrastructure/pg/repositories/`\n- Mapping functions in `infrastructure/pg/mappings/`\n- Migrations: append-only Go functions (never edit applied migrations)\n- All DB layer **95% code coverage**\n- Connection pool configurable via env vars\n\n**Schema (4 core tables):**\n| Table | Columns | Notes |\n|-------|---------|-------|\n| Users | id, user_name (UNIQUE), created_at, updated_at | |\n| UserProviders | id, user_id (FK), provider, provider_user_id, provider_email, created_at | UNIQUE(provider, provider_user_id) |\n| ShortenedUrls | id, user_id (FK), shortcode (UNIQUE), long_url, expires_at, created_at, updated_at | INDEX on shortcode, user_id |\n| UrlClicks | id, url_id (FK), clicked_at, ip_address, user_agent, referer | INDEX on url_id, clicked_at |\n\n### **4.6 app-auth.md**\n**Key Rules:**\n- **OAuth2/OIDC only** (Google, Microsoft, Facebook)\n- NO passwords, magic links, email OTP, or API keys for user auth\n- Backend: `markbates/goth`, `gorilla/sessions`, `golang-jwt/jwt`\n- OAuth state cookie: HttpOnly, SameSite=Lax\n- JWT tokens: stateless, required claims (user_id, user_name, sub, iat, exp)\n- Endpoints: `GET /auth/login/{provider}`, `GET /auth/callback`, `POST /auth/logout`, `POST /auth/register`\n- Frontend: `src/stores/auth.ts` with login(), logout(), handleCallback()\n- New users auto-registered on first login\n- Sign-in/sign-up in modal (never dedicated page)\n\n---\n\n## **5. OPENAPI SPECIFICATION**\n\n**File:** `/openapi/LinkShortener.json`\n\n**Endpoints Defined:**\n- POST `/auth/logout` - Logout (204 No Content)\n- POST `/auth/register` - Register new user (200 OK, returns AuthTokenBody)\n- GET `/user/urls` - List URLs (200 OK, returns ListUrlsResponseBody)\n- POST `/user/urls` - Create URL (201 Created, returns CreateUrlResponseBody)\n\n**Missing in spec (not implemented):**\n- DELETE /user/urls/{id}\n- PATCH /user/urls/{id}\n- GET /user/urls/{id}\n\n---\n\n## **6. LAYER SEPARATION SUMMARY**\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ FRONTEND (Vue 3 + TypeScript + Pinia)                   │\n│ ├─ DashboardView.vue (UI composition)                   │\n│ ├─ urls.ts store (state + API calls)                    │\n│ └─ DefaultService (generated API client)                │\n└──────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘\n                   │ HTTP JSON\n                   ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ WEB LAYER (routes/handlers/errors.go)                   │\n│ ├─ Request validation (Huma)                            │\n│ ├─ Viewmodel mapping                                    │\n│ ├─ Business handler calls                               │\n│ └─ Response mapping + error translation                 │\n└──────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘\n                   │ Pure Go interfaces\n                   ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ BUSINESS LOGIC (handlers/*.go)                          │\n<exited with exit code 0>"}}

